+## Recoverable dependency markers
+
+This coordinator is deliberately narrower than a generic transient-error
+policy. V1 recognizes only:
+
+- `4-execute` `ERROR reason=implementer_failed` when `execute.agent=codex` and
+  current-marker-bound evidence contains both HTTP 401 and recognized missing
+  bearer/basic-auth wording.
+- `ERROR reason=claude_launch_failed` when `exception_class` belongs to the
+  fixed launcher-origin `Hive::AgentError`/`Hive::TmuxRunner::*` allowlist and
+  the message matches a maintained session, readiness-handshake, or
+  Claude-runtime family with a non-destructive dynamic probe.
+
+The Claude exception allowlist is exactly `Hive::AgentError` plus
+`Hive::TmuxRunner::ExecutableMissing`, `NoServerRunning`, `CommandFailed`, and
+`CommandTimedOut`. Maintained message prefixes/families are: tmux session
+already exists/did not start; Claude tmux session terminated before ready or
+session no longer exists; could not inspect the Claude tmux session; Claude
+interactive prompt did not become ready; Claude binary not runnable; malformed
+Claude version output; Claude below minimum version; and Claude version-check
+timeout. A recognized-looking message outside those families has no probe and
+stays parked.
+
+Everything else stays parked: bare 401s, unknown launcher shapes, generic exit
+codes, test/business/review failures, merge conflicts, quota markers handled by
+the existing cooldown healer, and dirty worktrees. Worktree-owning stages
+require an empty `git status --porcelain`; brainstorm/plan state must be
+marker-only/empty scaffold. Live locks/controller slots, legacy layouts,
+missing/unreadable state, terminal-success content, marker rotation, and a
+failed mandatory task audit all reject recovery.
+
+The ledger key excludes stage and marker id, so restart, SIGHUP, stage movement,
+and marker rotation do not replenish the two-attempt lifetime budget. Attempt
+one may start on the first healthy observation. Attempt two requires both a
+different health fingerprint and 30 minutes after the failed first run was
+observed. At most one uncached project/classification probe group begins per
+full tick; a persisted cursor rotates fairness. Negative audits are emitted on
+decision/marker/fingerprint/recovery-epoch change, otherwise at most every 30
+minutes.
+
+Scheduling writes task `auto_retry_decision`, persists `reserved`, writes a
+`requestor=healer` request with trigger `auto_retry:<reason>:<attempt>`, then
+marks it `queued`. The child enters the ordinary `Commands::Run` task lock,
+repeats marker/content/worktree/config/dependency-signal checks, claims the
+token, writes the mandatory `started` audit, transitions the ledger to
+`started`, and compare-and-set clears only that marker before calling the
+unchanged stage runner. Existing project, concurrency, daily, quarantine,
+claim, and expiry gates stay authoritative. A dead started child that left no
+marker is restored only with `Markers.restore_if_none` on the same stage with
+no live owner.
+
+Set global `daemon.auto_retry.enabled: false` to stop scanning,
+reconciliation, probes, audits, reservations, and writes. Reload applies the
+switch without resetting the durable ledger. Operators can inspect paired task
+and daemon audit events and use [[commands/markers]] as the manual fallback.
+Task records use `event_type=auto_retry_decision` with bounded structured
+details. Daemon records use the closed events `auto_retry_evaluated`,
+`auto_retry_scheduled`, `auto_retry_queue_failed`, `auto_retry_exhausted`, and
+`auto_retry_reconciled`; both destinations carry the same decision/task/stage/
+marker/reason/classification/probe/fingerprint/attempt/action/rationale/request
+identity where applicable. Probe output is bounded, redacted, and control-safe;
+task events, daemon logs/rotations, queue requests, and the ledger are created
+owner-only independently of umask.
+
 Digest dispatches happen before status fetch because they are global, not
 project-row driven. The dispatcher tracks them with synthetic project/stage
 `digest/digest`; when the child is reaped, the scheduler advances its cursor
