 - **Per-task lock**: `<task folder>/.lock` — YAML payload `{pid, started_at, process_start_time, claude_pid?, slug?, stage?}`. Acquired EXCL by `Hive::Lock.acquire_task_lock` (`lib/hive/lock.rb:18`). Stale check uses `Process.kill(0, pid)` plus `/proc/<pid>/stat` field-22 cross-check to defeat PID reuse.
 - **Per-project commit lock**: `<project>/.hive-state/.commit-lock` — short flock around the `git add && git commit` in the hive-state worktree to serialize concurrent writers. See [[modules/lock]].
 
+## Recoverable dependency retry ledger
+
+Recognized Codex-auth `implementer_failed` and launcher-origin
+`claude_launch_failed` markers stay on disk while the daemon probes. A healthy
+decision creates a tokenized same-stage dispatch request; only the locked child
+clears the marker.
+
+Lifetime attempt/cadence state lives outside project state at
+`<state_home>/daemon/recoverable-marker-retries.json` (schema v1, file mode
+0600, parent mode 0700). Entries are keyed by project + stable task id (slug
+fallback) + reason, so stage moves and marker rotations cannot replenish the
+budget. The document stores attempts, marker episode and attrs, dependency
+fingerprints/probe summaries, reservation/request/token phase, backoff and
+exhaustion timestamps, recovery activity epoch, negative-audit signature, and
+the fair scan cursor. Writes use a sibling flock plus fsync/rename. Corrupt,
+partially shaped, unreadable, or newer-schema documents suspend automatic
+dependency recovery rather than resetting. See [[modules/daemon]].
+
 ## Runtime dispatch queue and web snapshots
 
 The daemon's producer queue lives under `$HIVE_HOME/dispatch_requests/`
